Presales Manager (France)
We are looking for a client-facing Presales Manager to help drive revenue growth as we continue our process of international expansion in France. Our solution (XTEL) covers predictive analytics, trade optimisation software, retail execution, business planning, and image recognition.
As a member of the presales team, you will assist in product demonstrations of our Trade Promotion Management/Optimization software solutions for global FMCG clients.
You will be accountable for supporting the presales process by shaping and scoping deals to satisfy customer’s requirements. You will also work closely with sales and delivery partners to define and scope quality solutions that drive business outcomes.
What you’ll do:
Provide advice and counsel to sales leadership in the effective use and deployment of technical resources;
Act as client representative along with Customer Success on internal Product huddles including collating user feedback/requests into product backlog to influence the roadmap;
Provide support of RFI and RFP processes;
Assist with the production and preparation of tailored Executive level product demonstrations/sales presentations;
Provide presales technical/functional support to prospective clients and customers while ensuring customer satisfaction with minimal supervision;
Provide direction and specialist knowledge in applying the technology/application to client business;
Collaborate and share information with presales peers and product life-cycle managers to inspire trust to customers by showing a consistent technical knowledge;
Understand customer problem statements and work with delivery teams to design the solution.
Who you are:
Strong exposure and understanding of sales life cycle, global delivery models (On-site/Off-shore etc.);
Capacity to collaborate effectively with multi-cultural, dispersed and multi-party teams & working within a matrix structure to harness capabilities of the team and craft a winning proposal /solution;
Sound experience demonstrating software tools and participating with the implementation/assistance of a system;
